{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_13","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' prompts/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Spec Cross-Critique\n\nYou have independent spec candidates in context from Gemini, Claude, Kimi, and DeepSeek.\n\nCompare them adversarially:\n\n- identify consensus\n- identify contradictions\n- identify missing acceptance criteria\n- identify App Store 4.3 risks\n- identify where a candidate would rebuild boilerplate infrastructure unnecessarily\n- identify testability gaps\n- identify vague or non-verifiable claims\n\nWrite `.workflow/iphone-app-factory/spec-cross-critique.md`.\n\nBe strict. A spec is not good enough unless an implementation agent can build and verify it without guessing.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
